cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of skin cancer detection and tracking using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also heavily relies on data synthesis techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper has potential clinical applications, which could place it in the cs.MED (Medical Imaging) category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of satellite imagery over time, which could suggest a connection to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
